				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pet commands are zone wide now. Except commands like /pet backoff /pet hold which require pet and owner to be fairly close. This is important point to know if you want your pet to attack or protect you while you wander through a zone and do not realize your pet has lost its way in the weird pathing. Periodically hitting /pet hold /pet backoff macro insures that your pet will not aggro on the first mob that AEs something and also lets you see pet say "/calming down master", proving the pet is nearby and if you are succesfull with that command there is no danger in having pet up even if it should wander off or be hit by a AE spell. The danger of pet creating a train is gone now. =) The danger of a mob warping and the pet pursuing and causing additional aggro before you can /pet hold /pet backoff still exists though =(</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
