				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">However, because of special rules designed primarily to prevent abuses of Charmed Pets, an NPC will almost always chose to attack a Player Character if one is within melee distance, even when a pet is at the top of its Hate List. It is not known precisely what these "special rules" are, but in practice they prevent pets from tanking in the presence of player characters within melee distance of the mob. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This was change almost 2 years ago. When first class balance talk started.
<br />
Mage was saying pet can't hold mob over his lvl away from mages. So they change it. and upgraded pet taunt. 2 days or so. there was a new patch to fix pet taunt once more. Corz pet taunt have many pet useless in grp and raid. It most of the time took away agro from Main tank. 
<br />
So the fix to this it what we have today. And PC in melee range NPC will allways hit PC. And ignor all pets so long a player on hate list is in melee range.
<br />

<br />
So this has nothing to do with charm kill of AoW 2 years ago (with made serval nerfs to charms spells)-</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
